Luanda — The Angolan veteran guitar player, Mário Arcanjo "Marito", member of the instrumental group, Kiezos, will be honoured on Sunday May 13 at Luanda?s Kilamba Recriational and Cultural Centre, at its programme dubbed "Muzogué da Tradição". Speaking to Angop on Monday here, Estêvão Costa, the head of the referred centre, said it is a special programme that will mark the artist's 70th birthday, one of the main icons of Angolan folk music. He said that the event will also count on the participation of other musicians such as Lulas da Paixão, under the instrumental back-up of Kimbambas do Ritmo, and Tony do Fumo son, whose instrumental base is under the responsibility Os Kiezos band.